# Windsurf Rules for vmanager Project

## CRITICAL: NO EMOJI POLICY
NEVER use emoji in any files, commits, or documentation.

## Project Overview
- Name: vmanager
- Version: 4.0.0
- Type: Proxmox VM Management Tool
- Language: C (C11)
- License: GPL-3.0
- Team: YXWA Infosec Lab (Crystal & evalEvil)

## Core Principles
1. High cohesion, low coupling architecture
2. Professional GNU coding standards
3. Zero compiler warnings policy
4. Efficient and elegant algorithms
5. Clean, maintainable code

## Code Quality Standards
- Use C11 standard
- Follow GNU coding style
- Zero warnings (-Wall -Wextra -Werror)
- Proper error handling everywhere
- No memory leaks
- Professional documentation

## Naming Conventions
- Functions: snake_case (vm_start, api_init)
- Structs: PascalCase (VMInfo, Config)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (MAX_VMIDS)

## Architecture
```
vmanager/v4/
├── include/vmanager.h
├── src/
│   ├── main.c
│   ├── core/    (API, config, VM ops)
│   ├── ui/      (CLI, TUI)
│   └── utils/   (Common utilities)
├── cJSON.c/h
└── Makefile
```

## Development Rules
- Always check return values
- Free all allocated memory
- Use fprintf(stderr) for errors
- Document complex logic
- Test thoroughly
- NO EMOJI anywhere

## Build System
```bash
./build.sh    # Build
make          # Alternative
make clean    # Clean
```

## Team Standards
YXWA Infosec Lab - Professional engineering, high quality, thorough testing.
